<h2>Elastos Installation and Boot Steps</h2>
    <p>Please see <a class="style1" href="../use_elastos.htm">Elastos&nbsp;2.0 installation and use</a> for preparation before installation.</p>
        <p><b>Step 1: </b>Install GRUB loader. GRUB loader can be installed in the following hardware: 
        <ul>
            <li>Floppy
            <li>Hard disk
            <li>Flash (Document does not describe in details)
            <li>Diskless start up server (Document does not describe in details)
        </ul>
            <p>For details of GRUB loader installation please see the article <a class="style1" href="setup_grub.htm">install GRUB loader</a>.
        <p><b>Step 2: </b>Modify the content of menu.lst file as needed.<br>
            <ul><p>Elastos.SDK already provides standard menu.lst file, but the user still needs to know how to write menu.lst, so as to modify Elastos start method as needed. Please see <a class="style1" href="intr_menu.htm">description about menu.lst file</a>.</p></ul>
        <p><b>Step 3: </b>Starts Elastos as needed through different methods, the methods to start are as the following: 
        <ul>
            <li>Starts Elastos from local.<br>
                Starts locally, i.e. start Elastos using Elastos system file stored in the hard disk or Flash device of this computer. Please see <a class="style1" href="BootElastosfromSelf.htm">starts Elastos locally</a>.
            <li>Starts Elastos through network (Network start up needs configure TFTPD service.User who needs network start up service please contact Koretide Corp.)<br>
                Starts Elastos through network is the most easy and efficient way to start. This kind of start method is good for Elastos system product development process. It is one of our recommended start up method. Please see <a class="style1" href="BootElastosfromNet.htm">starts Elastos through network</a>.
        </ul>
